England take on Sri Lanka in the sixth ODI of their series in Pallekele needing a victory to force a decider.

Joe Root's century on Wednesday secured a five-wicket victory for England in the fifth ODI to keep them alive, but they still need two more wins to avoid a series defeat.

Alastair Cook's men will be hoping to build on their victory in Pallekele to level the series at 3-3 ahead of the seventh ODI on December 16.

